The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Allsec Technologies has reported a profit after tax of Rs 3.96 crore for the quarter ended June compared with Rs 2.25 crore during the same period last year. Net sales increased 48 per cent to Rs 18.28 crore. The company has made a provision of Rs 5.28 lakh for paying fringe benefit tax during the quarter.

 Century Enka has posted a 34.69 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 8.58 crore for the three months ended June 30 against Rs 6.37 crore for the corresponding quarter in 2004-05. Total income has increased 6 per cent to Rs 241.53 crore.

 Mastek Ltd has clocked an 84 per cent rise in its earnings for the year ended June 30. It has posted a net profit of Rs 53.4 crore against Rs 29.1 crore in the year-ago period. The company?s board has recommended a final dividend of Rs 5.50 per share, in addition to the interim dividend of Rs 2 per share.

 Hindustan Petroleum Corporation has selected NCR Corporation for the automation of 165 of its premier Club HP outlets across the country. NCR will install its Octane 2000 solution, a business management system, specifically developed for the fuel retail industry. 

 Hyundai ELectronics has introduced a complete range of flat televisions in the east. The 15-inch colour television is priced between Rs 6,990 and Rs 7,990, while a 21-inch model costs between Rs 9,490 and Rs 13,990 and the 29-inch model comes in the Rs 22,990-24,990 bracket. 

 SAP India and IBM Global Services India have signed an agreement to train and recruit 850 certified consultants on SAP solutions.

